        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Public Health Service Ready Reserve Improvement Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill entitles members of the Ready Reserve Corps of the Public Health Service to certain rights and benefits concerning leave and pay that are provided to members of the Army Reserve and the National Guard who are employed by the federal government or the government of the District of Columbia. The Ready Reserve Corps provides trained personnel to respond to health emergencies and improve access to health services.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
